.TH "intel_dsb_indexed_reg_write" 9 "intel_dsb_indexed_reg_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_dsb_indexed_reg_write \- Write to the DSB context for auto increment register.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" intel_dsb_indexed_reg_write
.BI "(const struct intel_crtc_state *crtc_state "  ","
.BI "i915_reg_t reg "  ","
.BI "u32 val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc_state" 12
intel_crtc_state structure
.IP "reg" 12
register address.
.IP "val" 12
value.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used for writing register-value pair in command
buffer of DSB for auto-increment register. During command buffer overflow,
a warning is thrown and rest all erroneous condition register programming
is done through mmio write.
